# devenv's local profile/gc-root tree is a symlink farm into the Nix store
# (created by `devenv shell` / `direnv allow`, gitignored, not part of the
# workspace). Bazel's default package-discovery walk descends into it and
# chokes on foreign BUILD-like files it contains (e.g. a vendored upb
# source tree pulled in by a Nix package's debug symbols), which fails
# `bazel query //...` / `bazel build //...` / `bazel test //...` outright.
# Measured while authoring the CI lane (epic #87 M10.2): without this file,
# none of the wildcard bazel commands complete, in local dev or in CI once
# `devenv shell` has been entered at least once.
.devenv
# Same failure class, preemptively: several popular npm packages ship their
# own BUILD/BUILD.bazel files, which would break the wildcard package walk
# the moment `bun install` pulls one in (none do today — checked at epic #87
# PR review). Ignoring node_modules also speeds package discovery.
node_modules
